## Description

UD Veps-VWT is a manually annotated corpus of Veps made in Universal dependencies annotation scheme. The data is collected from [VepKar corpora](http://dictorpus.krc.karelia.ru/en/corpus/text) and consists of mostly modern news texts written in Central Veps dialect.




UD Veps-VWT is a manually annotated corpus of Veps made in Universal dependencies annotation scheme. The data is collected from [VepKar corpora](http://dictorpus.krc.karelia.ru/en/corpus/text) and consists of mostly modern news texts written in Central Veps dialect. The morphologigal annotations and grammar decisions are based on the language studies made by Riho Grünthal and different Veps dictionaries (by Nina Zaitseva). Many syntactic decisions are based on pre-existing Finnish, Estonian, Karelian and Russian treebanks.


## Acknowledgments

This work has been developed as part of the master thesis written by Käbi Laan in the University of Tartu with the help of supervisors Kadri Muischnek and Eva Saar.

## References

* Grünthal, Riho 2015. Vepsän kielioppi. Apunevoja suomalais-ugrilaisten kielten
opintoja varten XVII. Helsinki: Suomalais-Ugrilainen Seura.
* Zaitseva = Зайцева, Н.Г., Е.Е. Харитонова, О.Ю. Жукова 2012.
Орфографический словарь вепсского языка (Vepsän kelen orfografine vajehnik).
Петрозаводск: Карельский научный центр.

        <ul>
          <li>ADP: täht, polhe, taga, abul, edel, jäl'ghe, keskes, möto, päle</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Prep
        <ul>
          <li>ADP: Kacmata, ümbri</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<ul>
  <li><a>Clitic</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Ik
        <ul>
          <li>AUX-Fin: pidab-ik, voin-ik</li>
          <li>VERB-Fin: Muštat-ik, Oli-ik, Pagištihe-ik</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Ki
        <ul>
          <li>NOUN: venän-ki</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Se
        <ul>
          <li>ADV: kuna-se, kut-se, Äjak-se</li>
          <li>PRON: midä-se, kaikse</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<ul>
  <li><a>Connegative</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Yes
        <ul>
          <li>AUX-Fin: ole, olend, voi, voigoi, pida, sand, voind</li>
          <li>VERB-Fin: ajelkoiš, azotade, koskend, kül'mäiži, navedind, tekoi</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

      </li>
      <li>Word
        <ul>

          <li>NUM: kahesa, kaht, kaks', koume, ühtes, üks'</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

  <li><a>Typo</a>
    <ul>

        <ul>

      </li>

<h2>Syntax</h2>

<h3>Auxiliary Verbs and Copula</h3>

<ul>
<li>This corpus uses 1 lemmas as copulas (<a>cop</a>). Examples: olda.</li>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>This corpus uses 5 lemmas as auxiliaries (<a>aux</a>). Examples: ei, voida, pidada, olda, sada.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Core Arguments, Oblique Arguments and Adjuncts</h3>

Here we consider only relations between verbs (parent) and nouns or pronouns (child).
<ul>
  <li><a>nsubj</a>
    <ul>
      <li>VERB-Fin--NOUN-Nom (37)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--NOUN-Par (3)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--PRON-Nom (39)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--PRON-Par (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--NOUN-Nom (3)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--PRON-Nom (5)</li>
      <li>VERB-Part--NOUN-Nom (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Part--PRON-Nom (2)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<ul>
  <li><a>obj</a>
    <ul>
      <li>VERB-Fin--NOUN-Gen (3)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--NOUN-Nom (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--NOUN-Par (21)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--PRON-Gen (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Fin--PRON-Par (4)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--NOUN-Ade (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--NOUN-Nom (4)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--NOUN-Par (17)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--PRON-Gen (2)</li>
      <li>VERB-Inf--PRON-Par (4)</li>
      <li>VERB-Part--NOUN-Nom (2)</li>
      <li>VERB-Sup--NOUN-Par (1)</li>
      <li>VERB-Sup--PRON-Par (1)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<ul>
  <li><a>iobj</a>
    <ul>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>



<h3>Verbs with Reflexive Core Objects</h3>

<ul>
  <li>This corpus contains 1 lemmas that occur at least once with a reflexive core object (<a>obj</a> or <a>iobj</a>). Examples: löuta ičtaze</li>
</ul>

<h3>Relations Overview</h3>

<ul>
<li>This corpus uses 3 relation subtypes: <a>acl:relcl</a>, <a>csubj:cop</a>, <a>nsubj:cop</a></li>
<li>The following 13 relation types are not used in this corpus at all: <a>iobj</a>, <a>vocative</a>, <a>expl</a>, <a>dislocated</a>, <a>discourse</a>, <a>clf</a>, <a>fixed</a>, <a>compound</a>, <a>list</a>, <a>orphan</a>, <a>goeswith</a>, <a>reparandum</a>, <a>dep</a></li>
</ul>
